programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 5

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 6

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 7

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 8

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 9

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 10

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 9

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Message in a Bottle
programme.desc: A Jiridian probe headed for Earth is shot down by the Taelon Embassy and crashes outside of D.C. Liam recovers the probe, but he, Augur, and Julia are captured by another underground resistance movement led by the real Colonel Liam Kincaid.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Crossfire
programme.desc: As the election draws near, Liam believes Zo'or is trying to have Jonathan Doors murdered. The Resistance worries that an attack is imminent at the final debate. Julia mobilizes a group to protect Doors against Liam's wishes.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Crackdown
programme.desc: An unknown woman saves Augur and Liam from the raids on the Resistance. Lili sabotages the mother ship, but Zo'or stops its total destruction. Lili is reportedly dead. The investigation on the President's shooter continues.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: The Vanished
programme.desc: Some who were detained during the Resistance sweep have not reappeared after their release. Lili is taken to a lab run by Sandoval and implanted. Renee tries to help Liam find the missing people.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Emancipation
programme.desc: A group posing as volunteers attacks using a stolen skrill prototype that does not require an implant to control. It is discovered that the skrill queen is also missing. The investigation leads to a resistance group called Black Wednesday.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Déjà Vu
programme.desc: A joint Doors International/Taelon venture creates a machine that allows people to vividly relive a memory, but Liam suspects a back alley version of the device is leading to the death of some users.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: The Once and Future World
programme.desc: Artifacts believed to be Taelon are found in South America. Renee and Liam try to beat Sandoval to the source to determine the importance of the found pieces.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: One Taelon Avenue
programme.desc: Joshua Doors is running his own technology development company and Renee goes undercover to find out what is going on. An artificial intelligence program of the Taelons that controls human minds seems to be acting on its own.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Abduction
programme.desc: A volunteer who was working to interpret an ancient message from Ma'el assaults Da'an and escapes through a portal. Sandoval helps Da'an avoid interrogation from Zo'or while they try to locate her.

programme.desc: Years ago, Bobby was a rising star in the world of stand-up comedy. With thinning hair and a less than desirable wardrobe, Bobby's convinced his looks are no laughing matter. It's time for The Glam Squad and their experts to put Bobby back on stage.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: All The Right Career Moves
programme.desc: Nancy has now recovered from a long illness and is ready to reenter the workforce. Our experts give her the polish and edge she will need to land a new position. Will Nancy go from"left on the shelf" to being a"hot commodity" and look ten years young.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Blackbelt Beauty
programme.desc: Donna is a former Marine, a karate brown belt and a single mom with not much time for herself. Donna enters her journey with her "No Pain, No Gain" Marine attitude, and surrenders to The Glam Squad and their team of experts.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Trials of Tracy
programme.desc: Tracy is a New York City lawyer who can't find a man. Her frumpy wardrobe and thick glasses keep her home buried in her books for fear of rejection. But our team is on the case to bring this lonely lawyer out of her shell and gain some needed confidence.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Jayne Lowe
programme.desc: Woking wife and mother Jayne Lowe is at an all time low. After a high-flying career as an air-hostess, she has come down to earth with a bump, as a stay-at-home mum of three under-five's. Can Nicki Hambleton-Jones make Jayne look ten years younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Reconstructing Bernie
programme.desc: A construction worker by trade, Bernie is a man's man. So while years of backbreaking labor in the sun has taken its toll on his body, Bernie hasn't been taking care of himself. Time to make Bernie look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Donna Fuller
programme.desc: Derby wife and mum Donna Fuller is stuck at home and stuck in a rut. Her biggest problem is her gapped front teeth, which have left her, literally, with nothing to smile about. Can Nicky Hambleton-Jones and the team make Debbie look 10 years younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Bikini Special - Heather Williams
programme.desc: NHS Manager Heather Williams is the perfect candidate: after a weight loss of five stones and three years of four times a week gym workouts, all that remained of her former size 20 body was a sack of excess skin covering a tiny 4 foot eleven frame.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Singing A New Tune
programme.desc: April lost a front tooth in a horseback riding accident and never smiles. Her passion is singing, and she'd like to stand on stage without embarrassment. Will an orthodontic overhaul and a full Glam assault drop years from her appearance?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Independence Day
programme.desc: Recently divorced and about to send her daughter off to college, Candice is embarking on a new phase in life. Alone and worried about feeling old and unattractive, Candice has come for help to boost her spirits.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Debbie Ashcroft "One Year On"
programme.desc: 46 year old Debbie Ashcroft was a lifelong smoker and sunbed addict with the peculiar habit of bleaching her hair up to six times a week. A year later Nicky visits Debbie to find out if she's permanently kicked all the bad habits.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Sewing The Seeds To A New Look
programme.desc: Melissa has the perfect Beverly Hills fashion career, working with the finest made-to-order clothing. But when the exclusive clientele see her missing teeth, the impression is not what she would like. She also desperately wants to update her look.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: 80 lbs. Down, 10 Years To Go

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Caroline returns to find that all is not well at Leopard's Den. Danny has been putting a brave face on his ban but his attempts at helping out around the house are getting on everyone's nerves and Alice is finding his back-seat vetting especially hard.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: Danny is delighted to have his veterinary license back again and being back at work is helping to distract him from the impending anniversary of Sarah's death.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: Du Plessis is restless after his heart surgery but the family insist he needs to relax. Meanwhile Danny and Alice are happy to have closed down a zoo down that has been mistreating animals.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: While on honeymoon in London, Alice discovers that Danny has some final business to do before they can return home to Africa. He's reluctantly arranged to meet his estranged father, Robert, who has recently got back in touch.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Three surfing mates go missing in dangerous surf. The massive swell threatens to smash them onto the rocks in Sydney's Lurline Bay. The rescue crew is on a search and rescue mission but there's no sign of the surfer boys.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: A monster swell has trapped two teenage girls on the rocks at Sydney's North Head. As high-tide approaches, a daring double-winch rescue is their only option – to stop the teenagers from being swept out to sea.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: 55-year-old Gold Coast holidaymaker Irina is in real trouble - she's caught in a deadly ocean rip. Like many tourists, Irena was unaware of the risks of not swimming between the beach flags. The Gold Coast rescue helicopter spots her in the nick of time.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A head-on car collision in Tasmania has left tourists Hong and Xeu Wu fighting for their lives. Ambulance crews have managed to stabilize Mr. Wu but Mrs. Wu is in a critical condition and calling out for her husband.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 10
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 team are en route to the scene of a horrific accident. A pedestrian has been hit by a truck and is in a critical condition.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 11
programme.desc: A woman is badly hurt after being knocked down a bank by her pet goat, a man is found with serious injuries on a remote beach, and 11-year old girl has fallen down a bank and suffered suspected spinal damage.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 12
programme.desc: The chopper team is called out to save a motorbike racer who's crashed at 200ks per hour and a woman scalded by an exploding radiator, plus an elderly golfer in a kilt suffers a heart attack on the 18th hole.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 13
programme.desc: A 39 year old man has crashed his bike 15 kilometres south of Auckland city and an elderly man has collapsed while walking. He is unable to speak properly and is incorreherent at Waiheke Island.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 1
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 chopper team struggle to save a Paeroa farmer.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: A team of amateur scuba divers find themselves in deep trouble when their boat capsizes off Sydney's Botany Bay. The Westpac La Perouse crew spots the distressed divers while on a routine training mission.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 65-year old Dave, a surf skier, is attacked and bitten by a Great White shark while training in the ocean. Dehydrated (after four days at sea), Margo needs urgent hospital care.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: A car crashes another car at a country intersection. It's situation critical with four people trapped. It turns out someone was running from the police – and he was on drugs.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: Tasmania Police is on high alert after a prisoner escapes from jail. The man is armed and dangerous. The Rescue Helicopter is called in to assist with the manhunt. Things turn deadly when they spot him.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Hiker Robert had trained for over 6 months for the remote Cradle Mountain bush walk. With his young daughter in tow they set off on a 48 km walk. Three hours into the walk Roberts health takes a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 2
programme.desc: Tropical rain has hit Wellsford, flooding the entire town and leaving a pregnant woman and her unborn child fighting for their lives.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Salto Mortale
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept face a new mission: performing a front-flip through the air with a stuntman on board of an estate wagon. It's a new task for coordinator and adrenaline junkie Christoph Domi Domanski.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Remote Control
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept try out another new stunt: Stuntman Tobi, aka Heidi, operates an Artega GT at full speed with a remote control. This is, however, just a warm-up before the big stunt, in which he drives a car up a steep ramp.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Graduate
programme.desc: This is what it looks like when the Stunt Heroes from Action Concept perform a long jump: a vehicle jumps at full speed over four cars, which explode one after the other. It’s a matter of precision and timing.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Very First Time
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from the Action Concept are shooting a car rollover. But stunt coordinator Carl wants to go the whole hog. His motto: if you’re going to do something at all, you might as well do it properly!

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Highfall
programme.desc: While most people never had a car crash, they know spectacular car crashes with huge explosions from movies. But these scenes are much more sensational than in real life, because cars hardly ever explode.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Behind the Scenes
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept are tough professionals. They jump from houses and make cars fly or explode. On this episode, reporter Dean Malay takes a look behind the scenes of the stunt company.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Bike stunts
programme.desc: This time the Stunt Heroes from Action Concept deal with motorbike stunts: high jumps, risky drops and dangerous crashes. As usual, stunt coordinator Domi requires his motorbike specialists Daniel and Marcel to be in top form.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Ambulance
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept are always looking for new spectacular stunts and are not running out of options. Stunt coordinator Domi’s latest idea involves an old ambulance.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Matrix
programme.desc: Martial arts specialist Ramazan creates a choreography for a fight. It involves four stuntmen who need to disguise as secret agents and bash on him. Will Ramazan be able to free himself from this uncomfortable position?

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Multiple Collision
programme.desc: Fog, darkness and a pileup involving multiple cars: It's a scene that you can often see on highways and it's a scene that the Stunt Heroes from Action Concept want to recreate as part of a stunt with burning people.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The White Army
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept leave their headquarters behind and travel to a ski resort. Between the trees of a nearby forest they simulate the attack of an army of white-dressed soldiers.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Alarm in the Ski Resort
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept are still at their ski resort and party hard. This time they prepared a spectacular stunt involving a station wagon. It is thrown 50 meters into the air with a cannon.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Body Stunt Highlights
programme.desc: Today it's Action Concepts most popular and most spectacular body stunts: Jumping from rooftops, falling of a driving car, tumbling down stairs. Despite inevitable wounds, the legendary stunt crew enjoys the job.

programme.title: Supercars: 40 Years of BMW M
programme.desc: Supercars celebrates the unbelievable success of the BMW M Ltd. It all began in 1972 with the M1, one of the style icons of the supercars.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Limbo

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Take No Prisoners

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: The Second Wave
programme.desc: The Taelons decide to leave Earth when it appears that the Jiridians are invading. Meanwhile, a group of Resistance prisoners saved from the mother ship include several disguised Jiridians who are causing trouble for Liam and Renee.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Bad Moon Rising
programme.desc: Night before Halloween, a real-life nightmare unfolds when a young man is found clinging to life. The case takes a dark turn when Lt. Joe Kenda learns there is a second victim somewhere in the woods.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Death Comes Knocking
programme.desc: Neighbors are aghast when Ernestine Addison and her teen son Bobby are gunned down in cold blood. The case heats up when Kenda receives word that the killer’s murderous rampage isn’t over just yet.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Written in Blood
programme.desc: A community is shocked when Antoine McKenzie is brazenly shot outside an auto parts store in broad daylight. The only lead left for Lt. Joe Kenda is a final message written in the victim’s own blood.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: After School Special
programme.desc: Tragedy strikes when a beloved teacher is poisoned in her classroom. As doctors fight to save Barbara Lewis’ life, Lt. Joe Kenda and his team delve into her personal affairs.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Eyes Wide Shut
programme.desc: A park ranger discovers the corpse of amateur boxer Corey Edge floating in a shallow creek. Kenda learns the victim had ties to the criminal underworld, and investigates a rogue’s gallery of hustlers.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: My First Case
programme.desc: In his first case with the homicide unit, rookie burglary detective Joe Kenda volunteers to work a bloody multi-victim shooting deemed “unsolvable” by the veterans.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Bump In the Night
programme.desc: When a pretty, young pilot is found in bed, bound and with a bullet in her head, Lt. Joe Kenda must determine if this was a random assault or payback for something that happened in the skies.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Death Rains Down
programme.desc: Restaurant worker Sharon Coleman is murdered in a hail of large caliber gunfire. Kenda must break through a web of lies to hunt down one of the most dangerous criminal masterminds he’s ever faced.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Kobe, Banjo, and Kisses
programme.desc: An aggressive one-eyed Australian shepherd needs special treatment. A traumatized black and tan coonhound is terrified of people, a Maltese gets a little too excited when guests drop by.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Titan, Candy and Bella
programme.desc: A new puppy has "Young and Restless" soap star Michael Damian's cat cornered, MTV's "Downtown" Julie Brown wants to unspoil her Yorkie, and a 120-pound Rottweiler needs anger management training.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Cesar Conquers London
programme.desc: There's anarchy in the UK as Cesar faces a challenge from a rowdy Jack Russell, two culture-shocked pooches and an unruly Patterdale terrier mix.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Army Brats
programme.desc: At an army base, Cesar helps an Australian shepherd scared of men in uniform and a Shetland shepherd who barks non-stop when planes fly overhead.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: How to Raise the Perfect Dog
programme.desc: Cesar shows what it takes to raise four young puppies with different breed-related traits and how the importance of setting boundaries and rules at an early age can lead to a well behaved dog.
programme.sub-title: How to Raise the Perfect Dog

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Stanley, Shoven and Leo
programme.desc: Stanley, a surly Chihuahua mix, has a problem with attacking joggers. Two Pomeranians are known for their shrill barks. Shelter rescue Leo, performs a tight rope act when hearing a cough.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Hounds from Hell
programme.desc: Rescue dog owners need help with their hell hounds. Terrier Sammy, cries around skateboarders and large dogs, Sahzi, and a Belgian Tervuren, won't enter the kitchen or certain hallways.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to a Doll/Eats Plastic Bags
programme.desc: Robert, a 23-year-old man who's addicted to eating plastic newspaper bags, an addition so intense, that he goes days without food. Catherine, a 48-year-old woman whose best friend is a doll.
programme.sub-title: Addicted to a Doll/Eats Plastic Bags

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Casting / Psychics
programme.desc: Profiled are Kevin, who constantly covers his body in plaster casts even though he is not injured, and Melissa who is incapable of making a decision without a consulting a psychic.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: My Crazy Obsession Pilot
programme.desc: My Collection Obsession takes you deep inside the world of four of the country’s most obsessed collectors each taking their material obsession to jaw-dropping extremes.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: 5,000 Kids_Tickled Pink
programme.desc: Pat and Joe are passionate about their extreme collection of over 5,000 infamous kid dolls. Kitty Kay Sera is completely obsessed with the color pink. She even wears pink clothes and eats pink food.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Mouse Mania_Wigged Out
programme.desc: Janet has spent the last 30 years collecting over 5000 famous mouse memorabilia items and her collection holds the world record. Tamis has been obsessed with wearing wigs for the past 20 years.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: The Cat's House_My Oval Office
programme.desc: Frances and Bob share their house with nine felines who they raise like children. Ron is obsessed with U.S. presidents. He’s even built a replica of the oval office in his home.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Grown-Up Baby
programme.desc: Stanley, 31, has been obsessed with being an adult baby for the past 18 years. Every day he wears footie pajamas, eats baby food, wears a diaper and sleeps in a crib.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Mannequin Invasion_Carrot Queen
programme.desc: Chad Michael is a mannequin fanatic. His collection of over 300 mannequins has taken over every room of his house. Zizi has 35 carrot tattoos and she’s decorated every room with a carrot theme.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Spin Cycle_Newborn Dolls
programme.desc: Fred and Robert have a rare collection of vintage washing machines. They’ve over $40,000 to compile this one-of-a-kind collection. Lynn has created over 1,800 life-like vinyl newborn dolls.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Airline Addict_Crazy for Capybaras
programme.desc: Anthony has been collecting aviation memorabilia since he was 5. Melanie is crazy about her pet capybara, Gari, taking him for walks and teaching him tricks.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: My Crazy Obsession Christmas Spcl 1
programme.desc: My Crazy Obsession: Christmas Collection takes you inside the lives of extreme collectors who have taken holiday decorating to the max. For these obsessed collectors, it's Christmas year round.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Love Bunnies_ World's Strongest Family
programme.desc: The Best family is so obsessed with their own strength that they spend countless hours lifting weights. Candace and Steve's collection of bunny items has reached nearly 30,000 pieces.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Cruisin For A Bruisin
programme.desc: Join Jill and Marvin as they comb Belle River for the perfect floating home—something that’ll get them back in the swamps and back to their bayou roots.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Bayou Baby
programme.desc: Chris and Jessica are going back to their roots and looking for a bayou home near Houma, Louisiana. But with a rambunctious baby, finding the perfect waterfront home can be a challenge.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Cajun Bahamas
programme.desc: Mike Mazac and Kim Francis look for a Cajun camp where they can throw down and have a good ol’ time. Join these two as they cross lakes, navigate Bayous and motor through the Cajun Bahamas!

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Gumbo Shacks
programme.desc: Chef Brent Duthu and his father Danny are looking for a camp where they can catch speckled trout, one of South Louisiana’s delicacies right in their backyard.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Gator Country
programme.desc: T-Mike and Cayla want a new bayou home with enough room for their 300 pound pet pig. They need a place with water and a fence strong enough to hold this giant porker when he’s hot for a mate.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Fishing For A Bargain
programme.desc: Best friends, Drew and Nikki, are hopping aboard a boat and hitting the waterways looking for the ultimate fishing camp. But with floods and dangerous animals, the search can be a challenge.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Huntin' For A Bargain
programme.desc: James and Jennifer and their two kids raise Catahoula Cur hunting dogs in Northeast Lousiana. With 35 dogs, but only a half acre of land, they’re going to need a bigger home with space for the dogs.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Million Dollar Manor
programme.desc: Born and raised in the bayou, Floyd and Robin Foti are living the American Dream. Their small business grew to become a massive food market. Now they’re looking for a million dollar home.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: All-Terrain Livin
programme.desc: Josh and Tiffany Chambless grew up living the bayou lifestyle and spending any spare moment exploring the swamps on their ATVs. Now, they’re looking for a place that’s baby friendly.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Wake Zone Getaway
programme.desc: Ross and Sarah want a new bayou home where they can walk out their front door onto their fishing boat. They discover a house on an island can make getting there tough.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Cajun Cabins
programme.desc: Pat and Joyce want their own slice of the southern frontier. They're looking for a hunting cabin that has the wilderness he wants, but the space she desires.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Redneck Riviera
programme.desc: Spear fisherman Clay and his girlfriend Jackie are looking for their first home together around Pensacola, Florida, an area where the bayou meets the beach, known as the Redneck Riviera.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Mississippi High Rises
programme.desc: Matthew and Lindsey are looking for a camp of their own. Lake Mary houses can flood, so the couple is looking for a high rise home, lifted 20 feet off the ground!

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Backwoods Paradise
programme.desc: Life in the bayou is all about family and passing down traditions. Blane is looking for a place where he can spend quality time with his teenage daughter, doing what their family does best – hunting.
